article.headline: E. Illinois 65, Morehead St. 62
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Romain Martin scored 13 points to help break an eight-game losing streak as Eastern Illinois beat Morehead State 65-62 on Saturday. The Panthers (6-16, 2-11 Ohio Valley Conference) scored the game's first eight points of a 14-point lead. But Morehead State (10-10, 6-6) took its only advantage at 28-27 with 43 seconds in the first half on a Cordaryl Ballard jump shot. A 3-point play by Justin Brock put Eastern Illinois ahead 30-28 at the half. The Panthers led 60-52 with 1:34 remaining. But Morehead State, which dropped its fourth straight game, came within 64-62 with eight seconds to play. Mike Robinson was fouled and hit one of two free throws with six seconds left as the Panthers led 65-62. Jake Byre had 12 while Robinson finished with 11 and Ousmane Cisse was in double figures with 10 for Eastern Illinois. Brandon Callahan topped the Eagles with 18 while Jamyron Steward had 12.
